# ---- extensions that should never be served at this edge ------------------
^/.*\.(cgi|asp|aspx|jsp|jsa|cfm|pl)$

# ---- static-extension-cloaked probes (COMMENTED; threat-model §6 step-0) ----
# Hostile paths that END IN a .js/.css static extension, so the replay-corpus
# static-ext baseline absorbs them (docs/threat-model.md §6 step 0 surfaced these
# in the sanity gate). LEFT COMMENTED on purpose: a suffix rule on a static
# extension can false-positive on a real SPA asset of the same name -- enable
# each (drop the leading '#') only after a detect-mode FP check (work-stream B).
# Trailing volumes are from the 2026-06 corpus; comments stay on their own line
# so an enabled pattern is a clean PCRE2 line.
#
# ColdFusion CKEditor / admin probe (~160)
#^/cf_scripts/
# PM2 ecosystem config leak (~148)
#^/ecosystem\.config\.js$
# client/env config leak (~147)
#^/env\.js$
# server source leak (~134)
#^/server\.js$
# DB / server config leak (~200)
#^/config/(?:database|server)\.js$
